{"desc":["Random","Improving"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"At first, I was looking a similar characteristics of the shapes. Then, I moved to trial and error. If I see the points go up, I keep the shape. If it goes down, I remove the selected shape."}
{"desc":["Reliable"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"Same strategy. I couldn't get to 80-ish my first 15 rounds, so I just went with a solid 70."}

{"desc":["Random"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"I selected all of them and I removed a shape. If the points goes down, I readded them, and remove another shape. I got lucky and got 90 my first 10 tries. So I kept that."}

{"desc":["Cyclical","Improving","Fluctuating"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"I started by somewhat randomly seeing what combinations would get me points. Then, I started to remove or add items one at a time, and observed the changes to my point totals. Once I reach a high point threshold (>80) I tried to experiment by dropping and adding pairs of symbols. But that didn't seem fruitful, so I stopped."}

{"desc":["Improving","Plateauing"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"Once again, I started by broadly finding combinations of shapes that I hadn't tried. When I saw an improvement in my score, I honed in, changing each shape, one at a time. Once I hit 92, I tried to see if a subtle tweak would improve my score. It didn't. I decided to stick with what I had found."}

{"desc":["Fast","Plateauing"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"I quickly tried a random combination, which had a good base score, and then added some shapes. I selectively removed and added shapes until I hit 100. Since this was the maximum, I just kept rolling with it."}
{"desc":["Random"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"i was confused"}
{"desc":["Improving"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"I generally tried to change one thing per round unless I wanted to see a larger effect of a series of manipulations."}

{"desc":["Fluctuating","Improving"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"When there were less shapes selected, I typically added more shapes each time. When there were more shapes selected, I typically removed shapes. This round still consisted of trial and error."}

{"desc":["Reliable","Improving"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"I still used trial and error, but ended up selecting the correct combination for the most points. The location of the shapes on the screen seemed for the most part unrelated to the score."}
{"desc":["Reliable","Cyclical"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"Mostly experimentation, but when I felt I was beginning to understand I was towards the end."}
{"desc":["Improving"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"Building off of what I learned last round."}

{"desc":["Improving","Plateauing","Fluctuating"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"Tried to methodically add or remove shapes to improve the score. Stuck with the highest combination I could seem to get after a while. "}

{"desc":["Not Improving","Slow"],"otherDesc":"","learn":"I tried grouping shapes with similar features (eg round) but that didn't seem to matter. I found a combo with a fairly high score randomly and tried methodically removing/adding shapes to try to improve it. "}
